column5: Just got my first tattoo yesterday, Love it!

Well I must say that's cool!   Never had any ink done but something like that would get me considering one!  Hmm, the question quickly becomes which species?   Hard to pick favourites! Thanks for sharing.
Nice  Who did the art work for ya?
Andrew the owner of Skinner Ink in Barrie, I'm very happy with it, took under 2 hours... Renegade67 why not just get all of the species, lol
Just check their web. He dose some awesome work.  I have always wanted to get inked. My mudder says no. Im thinking at my age,I can make my own call.LOL
Very nice ink! Been contemplating on getting one myself...  Pete
Very nice work there looks great
Thanks guys, damn I should of said I could get him like 100 referrals, could of lowered my cost lol, it was a good price anyway.
Beautiful work, but what kind of fish is that supposed to be?
Nice man Andrews work is real good, I love some of his darker work.   My good buddy Shawn is also an artist at that shop
the day i turn 18 im getting a marlin tattoo similar to that they look amazing imo
Awesome. I want to get a pike as well but ive seen some bad ones. That looks pretty nice
